---
title: Honey Sriracha Chicken Legs with Basmati Rice and Green Beans
description: Do you like a little spicy with your sweet? Then you’re gonna love the sticky sauce that’s on this chicken. Honey and sriracha are a power duo, combining the hot sauce’s kick with finger-licking-good, glaze-like deliciousness. Because those flavors are the main attraction, we’re keeping the green beans and rice on the simple side (although we think they’re jealous of the action going on elsewhere on the plate).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/honey-sriracha-chicken-legs-da1df331.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/honey-sriracha-chicken-legs-5d5706120b44ec00090aaa87-1dbac698.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-sriracha-chicken-legs-5d5706120b44ec00090aaa87
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 750 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 48 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1020 mg
time required: 45 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Pat @chicken legs{16%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on a #baking sheet{}. Roast on top rack until browned and cooked through, ~{28-32%minutes} total. (We'll add the green beans after 20 minutes.)

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until softened, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Add @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

In #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, @honey{2%tablespoon}, and @sriracha{4%teaspoon} to taste. Cover with a #paper towel{} and microwave until slightly thickened, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}. Remove from microwave and stir in @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}.

Once chicken has roasted 20 minutes, remove sheet from oven; push chicken to one side, if necessary. Toss @green beans{6%ounce} on empty side of sheet with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. (For 4 servings, toss green beans on a separate baking sheet and roast on middle rack.) Return to oven until green beans are tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. In the last 3-5 minutes, remove chicken from oven and spread tops with half the glaze. Return to oven until glaze is tacky, ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} and season with salt and pepper. Divide between plates. Brush chicken with remaining glaze and place on top of rice with green beans to the side. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.